    "cycleDescription": "19PC treatment where Bulls are offered grass silage ad libitum plus 1.5 kg DM of concentrate per head daily over the winter period, turned out to pasture for 100 days, finished at pasture supplemented with 5 kg DM of concentrate per head daily for 100 days and slaughtered at 19 months of age - (this is the Winter housing period)",
